This appears to have been triggered by a server reboot undertaken during the morning of 09/16/23:

![image](https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-development/assets/1443986/143e98e7-7b8d-482f-b262-b7c0032531d4)

While the application is currently running on port 9000, this does not appear to be accessible beyond the localhost. I am trying to investigate if this is the reverse proxy:

```bash
[root@libtc201l ~]# curl http://127.0.0.1:9000/
<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

    <head>
        <title>Thesis Central</title>
        <meta charset="utf-8">
```

While the server was started, `httpd` runlevel must not have been set properly. I have restarted this:

![image](https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-development/assets/1443986/cdb98337-d0ab-48b0-adfa-cc9217944b27)

I can also confirm now that authentication using SSO is working as expected:

![image](https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-development/assets/1443986/1fd97a11-63d2-4807-8a9f-e6628a1240e4)

ThousandEyes monitoring service (maintained by OIT) has confirmed that the service outage has been resolved. I shall proceed accordingly, and reopen this should any additional errors arise:

![image](https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-development/assets/1443986/ffb70c51-436f-4871-92f0-98332036412e)

researchdata.title: Trainings from Libcal Display Wrong Scheduled Time

comments.body:
I met with Sarah Reiff-Connell in PRDS and we talked through several issues: 

- [ ] The Trainings event feed on the homepage (https://researchdata.princeton.edu/) is still displaying in UTC.
- [x] The Trainings feed is also displaying with the latest workshop date first, instead of the most recent, which they would like to change. 
- [x] The Trainings feed on the homepage is displaying events not using the internal tag "Princeton Research Data Service," so I'm not 100% certain that our internal tag RSS feed from LibCal is working. 
- [x] We'd like the events on this page (https://researchdata.princeton.edu/events-and-training) to display the most recent first and to pull in from the internal tag feed as well. It doesn't matter if past events are displayed. 
- [ ] Is there a way to pull in other campus groups' events into the PRDS website that isn't manual? (e.g. a feed from MyPU scheduler)
- [ ] Sending others RSS feeds of PRDS events that they can pull into external calendars (probably the internal tag RSS would work for this) 

It would be great if we could take a look at this next week @kevinreiss.
Even though the importer references New York/Eastern as the time zone for incoming date/time data it still seems to be thinking this data is in UTC time.
Does "other groups' workshops" equal feeds that are populated by applying tags to our libcal calendar?
